                <h1>Understanding Figure-Ground Relationship in Design</h1>
                <p>Figure-ground relationship is a fundamental concept in visual perception, where the mind distinguishes an object (figure) from its background (ground). This relationship helps us interpret complex images, allowing us to focus on the main subject while filtering out distractions. It's crucial in design, art, and psychology, influencing how we perceive and engage with visual stimuli.</p>
